#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:2
msgid "Getting started with MVSim"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:4
msgid ""
"**Goal:** Launch MVSim demo worlds both standalone and with ROS 2, and learn "
"how to interact with simulated robots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:6
msgid "**Tutorial level:** Advanced"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:8
msgid "**Time:** 20 minutes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:12
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:15
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:17
msgid ""
"MVSim ships with a collection of demo worlds that showcase different "
"features such as multi-robot simulation, sensor configurations, terrain "
"types, human actors, articulated vehicles and environment layouts. You can "
"run these demos either as a standalone application using the ``mvsim`` CLI, "
"or as a ROS 2 node that publishes sensor data and accepts velocity commands "
"through standard ROS 2 topics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:22
msgid "MVSim demo screenshots"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:26
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:28
msgid ""
"You should have MVSim installed following the :doc:`Installation-Ubuntu` "
"tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:31
msgid "Tasks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:34
msgid "1 Launch demo worlds with the standalone CLI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:36
msgid ""
"MVSim includes a standalone launcher that does not require ROS 2. This is "
"useful for quickly testing world files or for non-ROS use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:39
msgid "To launch the warehouse demo:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:41
msgid ""
"$ mvsim launch ~/ros2_ws/src/mvsim/mvsim_tutorial/demo_warehouse.world.xml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:45
msgid ""
"If you installed from binary packages, the demo files are typically found "
"under ``/opt/ros/rolling/share/mvsim/mvsim_tutorial/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:48
msgid "Some other demo worlds you can try:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:50
msgid ""
"``demo_turtlebot_world.world.xml`` -- A TurtleBot3 in a classic ROS-style "
"environment with obstacles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:51
msgid ""
"``demo_2robots.world.xml`` -- Two robots navigating among furniture blocks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:52
msgid ""
"``demo_elevation_map.world.xml`` -- A Jackal robot driving over terrain with "
"elevation data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:53
msgid ""
"``demo_greenhouse.world.xml`` -- A complex greenhouse environment "
"demonstrating XML loops for procedural content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:56
msgid "2 Controlling the robot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:58
msgid "Once a world is running, you can control the robot using:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:60
msgid ""
"**Keyboard:** Press W/S to move forward/backward, A/D to turn left/right, "
"and spacebar to stop. If the world has multiple robots, click on a robot in "
"the GUI to select it before using keyboard controls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:62
msgid ""
"**Joystick:** If a gamepad is connected, it will be automatically detected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:64
msgid "MVSim GUI control reference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:67
msgid ""
"The GUI also provides controls for camera view, simulation speed, and "
"visualization options. You can toggle orthographic/perspective view and "
"enable visualization of sensor data directly in the 3D window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:71
msgid "3 Launch with ROS 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:73
msgid "To launch MVSim as a ROS 2 node, use the provided launch files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:75
msgid ""
"$ source /opt/ros/rolling/setup.bash\n"
"$ ros2 launch mvsim demo_warehouse.launch.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:80
msgid ""
"This starts the simulator and creates ROS 2 topics for each vehicle and "
"sensor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:83
msgid "4 Inspect ROS 2 topics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:85
msgid ""
"With the demo running, open a new terminal and list the available topics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:87
msgid "$ ros2 topic list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:91
msgid "You should see topics such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:93
msgid ""
"``/robot1/cmd_vel`` -- Send ``geometry_msgs/msg/Twist`` commands to control "
"the robot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:94
msgid ""
"``/robot1/odom`` -- Odometry from wheel encoders (``nav_msgs/msg/Odometry``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:95
msgid "``/robot1/base_pose_ground_truth`` -- Perfect ground truth pose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:96
msgid ""
"``/robot1/<sensor_name>`` -- Sensor-specific topics (e.g., ``/robot1/"
"lidar1_points`` for 3D LiDAR point clouds, ``/robot1/laser1`` for 2D scans)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:97
msgid ""
"``/tf`` and ``/tf_static`` -- TF2 transforms following `REP-105 <https://www."
"ros.org/reps/rep-0105.html>`__ (``map`` → ``odom`` → ``base_link``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:99
msgid "You can send velocity commands from the command line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:101
msgid ""
"$ ros2 topic pub /robot1/cmd_vel geometry_msgs/msg/Twist \"{linear: {x: "
"0.5}, angular: {z: 0.3}}\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:105
msgid "Or use ``teleop_twist_keyboard`` for interactive control:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:107
msgid ""
"$ ros2 run teleop_twist_keyboard teleop_twist_keyboard --ros-args -r cmd_vel:"
"=/robot1/cmd_vel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:112
msgid "5 Visualize in RViz2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:114
msgid ""
"You can visualize MVSim sensor data in RViz2. Some launch files include an "
"``use_rviz`` option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:117
msgid "$ ros2 launch mvsim demo_warehouse.launch.py use_rviz:=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:121
msgid ""
"Alternatively, open RViz2 manually and add displays for the topics of "
"interest (e.g., ``LaserScan``, ``PointCloud2``, ``Image``, ``Odometry``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:123
msgid "MVSim depth camera visualization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:127
msgid "6 Headless mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:129
msgid ""
"For CI pipelines or remote servers without a display, MVSim supports "
"headless operation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:131
msgid "$ ros2 launch mvsim demo_warehouse.launch.py headless:=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:135
msgid "This runs the full simulation without opening a GUI window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:138
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Getting-Started-MVSim.rst:140
msgid ""
"In this tutorial, you launched MVSim demo worlds both standalone and with "
"ROS 2. You learned how to control robots with keyboard and ROS 2 topics, "
"inspect the published topics, and visualize data in RViz2. The next tutorial "
"covers how to define your own worlds with custom robots and sensors."
msgstr ""
